    "text": "You can keep both — the trick is paying for big runs deliberately instead of letting them tax your recovery by default. Yesterday's 86-minute run hit a load of 20.0, one of the biggest efforts your data shows, and the bill arrived this morning: recovery at 60, under your 67 target, with HRV at 46 ms versus your 30-day average of 50.5 ms and a suppressed weekly HRV trend. The unpaid part is sleep — 6.7 h last night, and your weekly average of about 6.8 h isn't much better, which is thin support for marathon-style volume. Two adjustments: follow long-run days with a genuinely easy day rather than moderate work, and bank longer nights before and after the big sessions. Protect those and the goal and the running stop competing.",
